This paper discusses the problem of low diversity in response generation for chatbots, which is a common topic in the field of natural language processing (NLP) and specifically in the subfield of conversational AI (cs.CL). The paper also proposes solutions to this problem using machine learning techniques, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the issue of model over-confidence, which is related to the topic of model calibration and uncertainty estimation (cs.SD).
